                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12444894" author="knutanders" created="Thu, 26 Oct 2006 15:05:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The eight minutes waiting for a lock timeout are only seen when running the BlobClob4BlobTest separately. When run as part of the All suite, the wait timeout is set to four seconds in ConcurrentTest&apos;s suite() method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since there are at least three tests which need a shorter wait timeout in order to complete within reasonable time (TestJDBC40Exception, BlobClob4BlobTest and ConcurrencyTest), it would be good to have a utility method that made it easier to change the timeout for a single test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12444918" author="djd" created="Thu, 26 Oct 2006 17:33:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The setUp method for BlobClob4BlobTest puts the connection in auto-commit false mode and then executes a number of statements but never commits them.&lt;br/&gt;
Either a commit() should be added or a comment explaining why a commit is not required. The code looks strange at the moment.,&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12444965" author="djd" created="Thu, 26 Oct 2006 20:17:47 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a utility decorator already to do this, see this code in ConcurrencyTest.suite()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        // Since this test relies on lock waiting, setting this property will&lt;br/&gt;
        // make it go a lot faster:&lt;br/&gt;
        final Properties properties = new Properties();&lt;br/&gt;
        properties.setProperty(&quot;derby.locks.waitTimeout&quot;, &quot;4&quot;);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        return new DatabasePropertyTestSetup(suite, properties);&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12445050" author="djd" created="Fri, 27 Oct 2006 01:32:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Revision: 468209 adds a utility method to DatabasePropertyTestSetup for setting the lock timeouts and sets BlobClob4BlobTest  to use it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12488950" author="knutanders" created="Sun, 15 Apr 2007 18:39:05 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in revision 468209.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
